latestPosts.caption:
Just a small appreciation post for my little brother. You all have mostly seen him recorded at 25 frames per second, I have lived with him 25 years of my life. 

People often say , I want to become like my father; like my mother or idolise their elder siblings. But I proudly here say, that I want to become like my little brother. There is a reason he is the most loved of our family. There is a reason his friends are there for him at every snag. He concatenates everybody together with his love and warmth. 

He has worked immensely hard for every step that he has climbed, for every title he has achieved, for every dream he has accomplished. As much as Hamid loves winning and absorbs the love that you all shower on him with utmost gratefulness , he also silently embraces the hate cause of his maturity to understand this coin of the entertainment industry comes with two sides. You just see one subject exposed to different vision. 

I have witnessed his first steps as a baby to bringing victory home in the biggest reality shows of the country. And I’m proud of every role he has played, sometimes to support, sometimes to traverse, sometimes to protect and sometimes to respect. 

Thankful to all of you giving my brother so much love and seeing through him even through your screens, we are indebted to the love and for everything else,how Hamid truly believes in this and says it all the time…. #UparWalaBidu …. ;)
